### .gitignore

Create a `.gitignore` file at the repo root with the following content:

```
# Node.js & PNPM
node_modules/
.pnpm-store/

# Build output
dist/
build/

# Environment files (do not commit secrets)
.env

# Log files
*.log
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*

# OS generated files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Lockfiles (if you prefer not to commit them, though many projects do)
pnpm-lock.yaml

# Generated report from backup_and_export.sh
repo_report.txt

# VSCode settings
.vscode/

# Temporary files
*.tmp